The paper deals with precoding design for massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of random matrix theory also suggests a possible categorization under statistical theory (cs.ST) or mathematical physics (math-ph). The focus on spatial correlation and signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) indicates a possible categorization under signal processing (cs.SI) and communication (cs.COMM).
